parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Lighting Control Module can cause the exterior lights, including headlights, taillights, and brake lights, to become inoperable, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights
taillights
or brake lights not working
intermittent lighting
lights turning off while driving
flickering lights
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Headlights not working
intermittent headlights
headlights turning off while driving
and difficulty seeing while driving at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to provide timely and effective recall repairs can lead to continued safety risks for drivers.
symptoms: Delayed or unavailable recall repairs
ineffective repairs
and lack of communication from the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Steering Shaft and Column
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the steering shaft and column can cause the steering wheel to seize or become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel makes a clicking or knocking noise
the steering wheel does not return to center after turning
the vehicle is difficult to steer
and the steering column is corroded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering fluid level is low
the power steering pump is noisy
the steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
and the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering linkage can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel makes a clicking or knocking noise
and the steering linkage is corroded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the LCM can cause the headlights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights may not turn on
may turn off intermittently
or may only work when the high beam switch is held. In some cases
the interior lights may also malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioner control module can cause the air conditioner to malfunction, leading to reduced comfort and potential health issues.
symptoms: The air conditioner may not blow air or may not cool properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the multifunction switch can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, leading to reduced safety and comfort.
symptoms: The wipers may malfunction
and the lights may turn on or off unexpectedly.
